
[{"ID":4759,"title":"Mindshare Labs launches open source trails app for Santa Fe County","status":"publish","type":"post","author":{"ID":3,"username":"mindshare","name":"Damian Taggart","first_name":"Damian","last_name":"Taggart","nickname":"Damian","slug":"mindshare","URL":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/company\/team\/","avatar":"https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/4b80aa96c59bcbe5b6af4431980a2435?s=96","description":"Over the past decade Damian has grown Mindshare Labs from a very small (spare bedroom) operation into one of the more established and sought after web design and app development firms in the Southwest. Mindshare Labs won Small Business of the Year in 2014 from the Santa Fe Chamber of Commerce. Before founding Mindshare Labs, Damian worked as a web and multimedia developer for St. John\u2019s College and Central New Mexico Community College, respectively. Damian has also worked doing freelance web design and internet\/technology consulting. He is an avid open source technology enthusiast.\r\n\r\nDamian serves the City of Santa Fe on both the Economic Development Review Committee and the Business and Quality of Life Committee. Additionally, Damian is a co-owner of the experimental arts collective <a href=\"https:\/\/meowwolf.com\/\">Meow Wolf<\/a> which has partnered with George RR Martin to open a 20,000 square foot art experience in Santa Fe.\r\n\r\nDamian graduated cum laude with an interdisciplinary degree in Media Arts and English from the University of New Mexico in 2003. Damian lives in Santa Fe with his wife Lara and two sons, Jack and Henry.","registered":"2011-07-29T22:06:45+00:00","meta":{"links":{"self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/users\/3","archives":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/users\/3\/posts"}}},"content":"<p>Mindshare Labs partnered with Santa Fe County to build an open source mobile app that details hiking and biking trails within Santa Fe County. The app contains maps for County, City, Forest Service, and private (Galisteo Basin Preserve) trails.<\/p>\n<p>The app\/map contains trail descriptions, elevation profiles, images, parking locations, and contact info. The map allows users to search for trails based on user type and include paved, soft surface single track, double track, trails and roads.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http:\/\/www.santafecountynm.gov\/news_detail\/2389\">Press Release<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenFuture\/OpenTrails\">GitHub repo (source code)<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/play.google.com\/store\/apps\/details?id=com.sftrails\">Google Play<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/itunes.apple.com\/us\/app\/santa-fe-county-trail-maps\/id1119349186\">Apple App Store<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","parent":null,"link":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/news\/mindshare-labs-launches-open-source-trails-app-santa-fe-county\/","date":"2016-08-29T17:51:14","modified":"2016-08-29T17:51:14","format":"standard","slug":"mindshare-labs-launches-open-source-trails-app-santa-fe-county","guid":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/?p=4759","excerpt":"<p>Mindshare Labs partnered with Santa Fe County to build an open source mobile app that details hiking and biking trails within Santa Fe County. The app contains maps for County, City, Forest Service, and private (Galisteo Basin Preserve) trails. The app\/map contains trail descriptions, elevation profiles, images, parking locations, and contact info. The map allows&nbsp;<a class=\"mapi excerpt-more\" title=\"Mindshare Labs launches open source trails app for Santa Fe County\" href=\"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/news\/mindshare-labs-launches-open-source-trails-app-santa-fe-county\/\">Read more &rsaquo;<\/a><\/p>\n","menu_order":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"date_tz":"America\/Denver","date_gmt":"2016-08-29T23:51:14","modified_tz":"America\/Denver","modified_gmt":"2016-08-29T23:51:14","meta":{"links":{"self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/posts\/4759","author":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/users\/3","collection":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/posts","replies":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/posts\/4759\/comments","version-history":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/posts\/4759\/revisions"}},"featured_image":null,"terms":{"category":[{"ID":3,"name":"Code","slug":"code","description":"","taxonomy":"category","parent":{"ID":6,"name":"News","slug":"news","description":"","taxonomy":"category","parent":null,"count":77,"link":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/category\/news\/","meta":{"links":{"collection":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms","self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms\/280"}}},"count":14,"link":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/category\/news\/code\/","meta":{"links":{"collection":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms","self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms\/3"}}},{"ID":4,"name":"Downloads","slug":"downloads","description":"","taxonomy":"category","parent":{"ID":6,"name":"News","slug":"news","description":"","taxonomy":"category","parent":null,"count":77,"link":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/category\/news\/","meta":{"links":{"collection":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms","self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms\/280"}}},"count":21,"link":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/category\/news\/downloads\/","meta":{"links":{"collection":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms","self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms\/4"}}},{"ID":6,"name":"News","slug":"news","description":"","taxonomy":"category","parent":null,"count":77,"link":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/category\/news\/","meta":{"links":{"collection":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms","self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/category\/terms\/280"}}}]}},{"ID":4638,"title":"Rebranding Mindshare","status":"publish","type":"post","author":{"ID":3,"username":"mindshare","name":"Damian Taggart","first_name":"Damian","last_name":"Taggart","nickname":"Damian","slug":"mindshare","URL":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/company\/team\/","avatar":"https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/4b80aa96c59bcbe5b6af4431980a2435?s=96","description":"Over the past decade Damian has grown Mindshare Labs from a very small (spare bedroom) operation into one of the more established and sought after web design and app development firms in the Southwest. Mindshare Labs won Small Business of the Year in 2014 from the Santa Fe Chamber of Commerce. Before founding Mindshare Labs, Damian worked as a web and multimedia developer for St. John\u2019s College and Central New Mexico Community College, respectively. Damian has also worked doing freelance web design and internet\/technology consulting. He is an avid open source technology enthusiast.\r\n\r\nDamian serves the City of Santa Fe on both the Economic Development Review Committee and the Business and Quality of Life Committee. Additionally, Damian is a co-owner of the experimental arts collective <a href=\"https:\/\/meowwolf.com\/\">Meow Wolf<\/a> which has partnered with George RR Martin to open a 20,000 square foot art experience in Santa Fe.\r\n\r\nDamian graduated cum laude with an interdisciplinary degree in Media Arts and English from the University of New Mexico in 2003. Damian lives in Santa Fe with his wife Lara and two sons, Jack and Henry.","registered":"2011-07-29T22:06:45+00:00","meta":{"links":{"self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/users\/3","archives":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/users\/3\/posts"}}},"content":"<p>We are currently working on a rebranding initiative. Our new name and logo is being rolled out now through the end of August, so there will be some references to Mindshare Studios\u00a0and Mindshare Labs until the transition is complete.<\/p>\n<p>Say hi to<br \/>\n<strong>mindshare labs.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong><img src=\"https:\/\/gallery.mailchimp.com\/bf1d0f5bebb27fa15f1c84adb\/images\/78e77fb1-064b-47bf-96ea-43b234357c2c.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" align=\"center\" data-cke-saved-src=\"https:\/\/gallery.mailchimp.com\/bf1d0f5bebb27fa15f1c84adb\/images\/78e77fb1-064b-47bf-96ea-43b234357c2c.png\" \/><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>You will soon be seeing a lot more of this brand identity as we take the steps to fully convert. Rest assured that we are the same team who has supported your website or online project throughout the years of our partnership.<\/p>\n","parent":null,"link":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/news\/rebranding-mindshare\/","date":"2016-07-06T11:19:44","modified":"2016-07-06T14:00:49","format":"standard","slug":"rebranding-mindshare","guid":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/?p=4638","excerpt":"<p>We are currently working on a rebranding initiative. Our new name and logo is being rolled out now through the end of August, so there will be some references to Mindshare Studios\u00a0and Mindshare Labs until the transition is complete. Say hi to mindshare labs. You will soon be seeing a lot more of this brand&nbsp;<a class=\"mapi excerpt-more\" title=\"Rebranding Mindshare\" href=\"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/news\/rebranding-mindshare\/\">Read more &rsaquo;<\/a><\/p>\n","menu_order":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"date_tz":"America\/Denver","date_gmt":"2016-07-06T17:19:44","modified_tz":"America\/Denver","modified_gmt":"2016-07-06T20:00:49","meta":{"links":{"self":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/posts\/4638","author":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/users\/3","collection":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/posts","replies":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/posts\/4638\/comments","version-history":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/posts\/4638\/revisions"}},"featured_image":null,"terms":{"post_tag":[{"ID":292,"name":"10 years","slug":"10-years","description":"","taxonomy":"post_tag","parent":null,"count":1,"link":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/tag\/10-years\/","meta":{"links":{"collection":"https:\/\/mind.sh\/are\/wp-json\/taxonomies\/post_tag\/terms","self"